# Figma Design System Rules – StatementFlow Frontend

## Design System Structure

### Token Definitions

- Design tokens are defined in `src/app/globals.css`.
- **Colors:** `:root` exposes `--background` and `--foreground`; light/dark are switched via `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)`.
- **Theme mapping:** `@theme inline` maps CSS variables for Tailwind: `--color-background`, `--color-foreground`, `--font-sans` (Geist), `--font-mono` (Geist Mono).
- **IMPORTANT:** Prefer Tailwind theme colors `bg-background`, `text-foreground` and semantic zinc utilities (`text-zinc-600`, `dark:text-zinc-400`, `border-zinc-200`, `dark:border-zinc-800`) over hardcoded hex. Add new tokens to `globals.css` and `@theme inline` when the design system grows.

### Component Library

- **UI primitives:** `src/components/ui/` — Button, Input, Appear, PageAppear, ScrollReveal.
- **Layout:** `src/components/layout/` — SiteHeader, StatementFlowLogo.
- **Feature areas:** `src/components/auth/`, `src/components/dashboard/`, `src/components/landing/`.
- **IMPORTANT:** Reuse `Button` from `@/components/ui/button` with `variant?: "primary" | "secondary" | "ghost"` and `Input` from `@/components/ui/input` instead of building new form controls.
- New UI components belong in `src/components/ui/`; feature-specific components in the appropriate folder (auth, dashboard, landing).
- Components use PascalCase and default export is not required; named exports are used (e.g. `export function Button`).
- **IMPORTANT:** All interactive components that use hooks or browser APIs must start with `"use client";`.

### Frameworks & Libraries

- **Stack:** Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript.
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4 (`@import "tailwindcss"` in `globals.css`).
- **Utilities:** `clsx` for conditional `className` composition.
- **Icons:** `lucide-react` — use named imports (e.g. `FileCheckCorner`). Do not add new icon packages; use Lucide or assets from Figma.

### Styling Approach

- Use Tailwind utility classes only; no inline styles for layout/colors.
- Prefer semantic tokens: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, and zinc scale for borders/secondary text (`zinc-200`, `zinc-600`, `dark:zinc-800`, etc.).
- Global styles and theme are in `src/app/globals.css`; body uses `var(--background)` and `var(--foreground)`.
- Responsive: use Tailwind breakpoints (`md:`, `lg:`) and mobile-first classes.
- Rounded corners: prefer `rounded-full` for pills/buttons, `rounded-xl` or `rounded-2xl` for cards/inputs to match existing UI.

### Project Structure & Imports

- Use path alias `@/` for all internal imports: `@/components/`, `@/lib/`.
- Group imports: React/Next, third-party, then `@/` (components, lib).
- App routes live under `src/app/` (page.tsx, layout.tsx).

